</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C0942E3574BFFAFFEB55B6CFD232075" authority="Simon, 1901" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1901" box="[298,660,292,316]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Atelurius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="12" pageNumber="443" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="segmentatus">
<emphasis id="B97DE572574BFFAFFEB55B6CFDBD2072" box="[298,522,292,316]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="443">Atelurius segmentatus</emphasis>
Simon, 1901
</taxonomicName>
, by original designation.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB63960574BFFAFFF085B21FA3E235D" blockId="12.[151,1436,361,532]" pageId="12" pageNumber="443">
<emphasis id="B97DE572574BFFAFFF085B21FEC520CA" bold="true" box="[151,370,361,387]" pageId="12" pageNumber="443">Revised diagnosis.</emphasis>
Males of 
<taxonomicName id="4C0942E3574BFFAFFE7B5B22FDFC20CD" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1901" box="[484,587,362,388]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Atelurius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="12" pageNumber="443" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97DE572574BFFAFFE7B5B22FDFC20CD" box="[484,587,362,388]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="443">Atelurius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be identified by the short RvTA, totally covered by denticles (
<figureCitation id="133225E5574BFFAFFAA65B22FF0020E0" captionStart="FIGURES 59–64" captionStartId="19.[151,264,1908,1932]" captionTargetBox="[192,1396,181,1884]" captionTargetId="figure-18@19.[192,1396,181,1884]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURES 59–64. Scanning electronic microscopy (SEM). Male palp of Guriurius minuano sp. nov. (MCTP 38993): 59 ventral view, arrow: tegulum depression; 60 ventral view, arrow: ventral surface RvTA. Male palp of At. segmentatus (MCN 36806): 61 ventral view; 62 detail of RvTA dorsal surface. Male palp of Si. gladifer (MCTP 31078): 63 ventral view, arrow: tegulum depression; 64 details of RvTA arrow: RvTA ventral surface." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6417700" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6417700/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="443">Figs 61– 62</figureCitation>
). Males of 
<taxonomicName id="4C0942E3574BFFAFFEAB5BC6FE2C20E1" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1901" box="[308,411,398,424]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Atelurius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="12" pageNumber="443" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97DE572574BFFAFFEAB5BC6FE2C20E1" box="[308,411,398,424]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="443">Atelurius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differ from those of 
<taxonomicName id="4C0942E3574BFFAFFD1C5BC6FD5A20E1" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1901" box="[643,749,398,424]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Scoturius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="12" pageNumber="443" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97DE572574BFFAFFD1C5BC6FD5A20E1" box="[643,749,398,424]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="443">Scoturius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C0942E3574BFFAFFCBC5BC7FC3020E1" authorityName="Ruiz &amp; Maddison" authorityYear="2015" box="[803,903,399,424]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Urupuyu" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="12" pageNumber="443" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97DE572574BFFAFFCBC5BC7FC3020E1" box="[803,903,399,424]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="443">Urupuyu</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by not having a bilobed RTA; differ from those of 
<taxonomicName id="4C0942E3574BFFAFFF275BFBFEB12085" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1901" box="[184,262,435,460]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Hurius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="12" pageNumber="443" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97DE572574BFFAFFF275BFBFEB12085" box="[184,262,435,460]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="443">Hurius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C0942E3574BFFAFFEDE5BFAFE762085" authorityName="Galiano" authorityYear="1988" box="[321,449,434,460]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Simonurius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="12" pageNumber="443" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97DE572574BFFAFFEDE5BFAFE762085" box="[321,449,434,460]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="443">Simonurius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having a sub-triangular RTA. Males of 
<taxonomicName id="4C0942E3574BFFAFFC2B5BFAFBAC2085" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1901" box="[948,1051,434,460]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Atelurius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="12" pageNumber="443" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97DE572574BFFAFFC2B5BFAFBAC2085" box="[948,1051,434,460]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="443">Atelurius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differ from those of 
<taxonomicName id="4C0942E3574BFFAFFA8F5BFAFA2B2085" authorityName="Galiano" authorityYear="1988" box="[1296,1436,434,460]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Admesturius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="12" pageNumber="443" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97DE572574BFFAFFA8F5BFAFA2B2085" box="[1296,1436,434,460]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="443">Admesturius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having a longer embolus and shorter RvTA. Females of 
<taxonomicName id="4C0942E3574BFFAFFCAA5B9EFC2B20B9" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1901" box="[821,924,470,496]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Atelurius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="12" pageNumber="443" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97DE572574BFFAFFCAA5B9EFC2B20B9" box="[821,924,470,496]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="443">Atelurius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differ from those of other huriines by having longer copulatory ducts with the proximal section membranous (
<figureCitation id="133225E5574BFFAFFCF45BB2FC0B235D" box="[875,956,506,532]" captionStart="FIGURES 43–48" captionStartId="14.[151,264,1931,1955]" captionTargetBox="[165,1411,691,1889]" captionTargetId="figure-217@14.[151,1435,669,1907]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 43–48. Female of Atelurius segmentatus. Habitus (MCN 36915): 43 dorsal view, white arrow: chevrons coloration pattern; 44 ventral view, white arrow: ventrally chitinized plate; 45 lateral view; 46 face, frontal view. Scale bars: 1 mm. Epigyne female 47 ventral; 48 dorsal. Scale bars: 0.10 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6417694" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6417694/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="443">Fig. 48</figureCitation>
) and poorly differentiated spermathecae.
</paragraph>
